# MVC Structure

Follow this on **every** feature, fix, and refactor. Do not dump logic into `App.jsx`.

## Client (`src/`) — required now

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| View | `views/` | Presentational UI only (JSX, styling, props) |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Hooks: state, events — call services + models — no JSX |
| Service | `services/` | HTTP / API calls (`fetch`), response wiring — no JSX |
| Model | `models/` | Validation, form shapes, mappers, static lists, constants |
| Config | `config/` | API base URL and client config |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `views` → `controllers` → `services` → API  
          ↘ `models` (validation, constants, mapping helpers)

Services may call model mappers to shape API data. Controllers call services for network work and models for local rules/data.

## Server (`server/`)

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| Model | `models/` | DB queries and data access |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Request handling, call models, shape responses |
| Routes | `routes/` | Wire HTTP paths to controllers only |
| Config | `config/` | DB and env setup |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `routes` → `controllers` → `models`

Do not put route handlers in `server/index.js`.

## Mandatory checklist (every prompt)

1. New feature → matching files in the correct layers.
2. Views: no `fetch`, no business rules, no hardcoded data lists — use controllers.
3. Controllers: no SQL, no JSX/HTML markup, no raw `fetch` — use services.
4. Services: HTTP only (plus thin wiring to model mappers); no React hooks/JSX.
5. Models: no `fetch`/HTTP; no JSX. Validation, forms, static lists, and mappers belong here.
6. Prefer extending this layout over one-off folders at the root of `src/` or `server/`.
